00:39:40.390 --> 00:39:43.336
because the colors flip-flop.

00:39:43.360 --> 00:39:46.640
So on one side, on is in
white; in the other it's blue.

00:39:46.640 --> 00:39:48.260
So is it actually on?

00:39:48.260 --> 00:39:49.510
Is it actually off?

00:39:49.920 --> 00:39:54.776
It's very unclear as to how to actually
figure out what is going on here.

00:39:54.800 --> 00:39:56.760
So I think that would
be a really big issue both

00:39:56.760 --> 00:39:59.530
from a privacy perspective,
because you can't understand

00:39:59.530 --> 00:40:03.996
what's turned on or off, and then
also from an accessibility perspective

00:40:04.020 --> 00:40:05.740
as well.

00:40:06.050 --> 00:40:08.410
Now this one is actually
a great one as well.

00:40:08.410 --> 00:40:12.926
It says, We use cookies to offer
you a better browsing experience,

00:40:12.950 --> 00:40:17.240
analyze side traffic, and personalize
content, and serve targeted ads.

00:40:18.090 --> 00:40:20.540
By continuing to browse
the website, you will continue

00:40:20.560 --> 00:40:23.810
to our use cookies, and then
you click continue to browse.

00:40:24.190 --> 00:40:27.870
So this actually does not
obtain any consent whatsoever,

00:40:28.280 --> 00:40:31.030
meaning that this is not
sufficient to establish consent

00:40:31.030 --> 00:40:34.350
under privacy laws because
nonactivity is not sufficient

00:40:34.350 --> 00:40:35.510
to establish consent.

00:40:35.960 --> 00:40:38.280
So these types of banners
definitely need to go.

00:40:38.280 --> 00:40:41.296
We call them placebo banners
because they don't allow user

00:40:41.320 --> 00:40:45.150
any actual choice, and the
cookies are applied to their device,

00:40:45.150 --> 00:40:47.376
regardless of what they
actually choose here.

00:40:47.400 --> 00:40:47.900
<v Hans> Yes.

00:40:47.900 --> 00:40:50.310
And for anyone who's thinking,
I just don't want to comply

00:40:50.310 --> 00:40:51.200
with privacy laws.

00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:53.150
Well, just don't even
have these fake banners.

00:40:53.150 --> 00:40:55.090
Like, just bring people... I mean,
if you're going to track them,

00:40:55.090 --> 00:40:58.080
you're going to track them; you
don't even need a banner then.

00:40:58.080 --> 00:41:00.670
<v Donata> This helps no one.

00:41:01.760 --> 00:41:04.940
Keeping accessibility in mind
with your cooking consent banner.

00:41:04.940 --> 00:41:06.230
Hans, you want to take this one?

00:41:06.230 --> 00:41:08.300
<v Hans> Yes, absolutely.

00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:13.710
For example, when you click
tab, the very first thing that happens

00:41:13.710 --> 00:41:16.360
on the website is you're brought
right into the consent mechanism.

00:41:16.360 --> 00:41:18.280
And that's very common
because you want

00:41:18.280 --> 00:41:21.910
to understand people's consent
choices prior to them interacting

00:41:21.910 --> 00:41:23.090
with the rest of your website.

00:41:23.510 --> 00:41:26.590
This is very common if you have
analytics tools on your website

00:41:26.590 --> 00:41:28.880
where you want to get
consent sooner than later

00:41:28.880 --> 00:41:31.620
so that you can understand how
people interact with your website.

00:41:32.160 --> 00:41:35.266
I always say there's nothing
wrong with collecting analytics data

00:41:35.290 --> 00:41:37.426
or sending targeted
advertisements.

00:41:37.450 --> 00:41:39.280
I love targeted
advertisements personally.

00:41:39.650 --> 00:41:41.196
I know you hate
them, but I love them.

00:41:41.220 --> 00:41:42.560
I love them when
they're relevant to me.

00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:46.266
But what I like as a person
is the ability to choose

00:41:46.290 --> 00:41:47.930
who sends me targeted ads.

00:41:48.770 --> 00:41:52.680
But as you tab through these
options, you're brought to each

00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:54.886
and every section so
that you get a choice,

00:41:54.910 --> 00:41:58.086
whether you are navigating
with a mouse or a screen reader,

00:41:58.110 --> 00:42:01.510
you can choose marketing or
functional cookies, you can choose

00:42:01.510 --> 00:42:02.986
to enable or disable them.

00:42:03.010 --> 00:42:05.410
You can access the privacy
policy or more information

00:42:05.410 --> 00:42:06.440
which are underlined.

00:42:06.820 --> 00:42:09.690
And then you have the clear
safe settings, deny button

00:42:09.690 --> 00:42:11.036
and accept all button.

00:42:11.060 --> 00:42:13.270
And last but not least, you
have the ability just to close out

00:42:13.270 --> 00:42:14.410
in the top right corner.

00:42:14.410 --> 00:42:18.030
So being able to navigate
a consent banner is just

00:42:18.030 --> 00:42:21.296
as essential as ensuring you're
getting consent in the first place,

00:42:21.320 --> 00:42:24.350
because it all comes back to
wanting to ensure people have access

00:42:24.350 --> 00:42:26.240
to your website, and
they have the ability

00:42:26.240 --> 00:42:29.020
to set their privacy preferences
when visiting your website.

00:42:29.020 --> 00:42:31.800
<v Donata> And most cookie
consent providers will state

00:42:31.800 --> 00:42:35.050
on their website whether or
not they're accessibility compliant

00:42:35.050 --> 00:42:39.580
so make sure to keep
an eye out on that as well.

00:42:39.580 --> 00:42:43.990
Obtaining a must draw in consent.
So you need to get a consent

00:42:43.990 --> 00:42:46.950
to email marketing
for many privacy laws,

00:42:47.420 --> 00:42:50.556
and many individuals have the
right to withdraw that consent.

00:42:50.580 --> 00:42:55.416
So consent must be provided in a
way that a consumer can say yes or no,

00:42:55.440 --> 00:42:58.040
and it must not be confusing,
and must be accessible.

00:42:58.510 --> 00:43:01.326
So here you have an email
marketing subscription form,

00:43:01.350 --> 00:43:04.716
and the user must opt out if they
do not want to receive messages

00:43:04.740 --> 00:43:06.340
instead of being
allowed to opt in.

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:09.920
So here it says, choose how
we send you marketing messages.

00:43:09.920 --> 00:43:12.670
Check the box if you don't
want us to tell you about offers,

00:43:12.670 --> 00:43:15.430
rewards, and information
about products or services.

00:43:15.910 --> 00:43:19.850
We'll never share details with anyone
else without your permission. Lie.

00:43:20.290 --> 00:43:24.840
Now, when it comes to privacy
law compliance, most privacy laws

00:43:24.840 --> 00:43:29.030
such as GDPR do require
email marketing to be opt in.

00:43:29.560 --> 00:43:31.650
So you cannot opt
in people by default.

00:43:31.650 --> 00:43:34.460
They must opt in themselves
if they would like to.

00:43:34.900 --> 00:43:37.490
So you need to allow people
to opt in and also allow them

00:43:37.490 --> 00:43:38.520
to opt out as well.

00:43:38.520 --> 00:43:41.480
<v Hans> Yes, this is one of
